Phase 1 is complete and working well. I'd like to continue building the project without changing anything that already works.

In this phase I'd like to build a proper dataset management layer that will become the foundation for the pivot engine.

Right now uploaded Excel files can be previewed. Instead of treating them as temporary uploads, I'd like the application to manage them as reusable datasets.

Please implement the following.

When an Excel file is uploaded:

- Read every sheet in the workbook.
- Store metadata about the workbook.
- Store metadata about each sheet.
- Store metadata about every column.

I don't want to repeatedly inspect the Excel file every time a pivot is generated. The application should know the dataset structure beforehand.

For every column, automatically detect the datatype.

Support at least these datatypes:

- Text
- Integer
- Decimal
- Date
- Boolean

If a column contains Excel dates or values that pandas can reliably identify as dates, treat it as a Date column.

Also determine whether each column is nullable.

Create separate database tables for:

Datasets
Sheets
Columns

Each dataset should know:

- filename
- stored filename
- upload timestamp
- total sheets
- total rows
- total columns

Each sheet should know:

- dataset
- sheet name
- row count

Each column should know:

- dataset
- sheet
- column name
- datatype
- nullable

Next I'd like a Dataset Management page.

This page should show:

A list of uploaded datasets.

When I select a dataset, I should see:

- workbook information
- available sheets
- total rows
- total columns

When I select a sheet, I should see:

- first 100 rows
- column names
- detected datatypes

Please create clean REST APIs for this page.

I'd like APIs to:

- list datasets
- get dataset details
- list sheets
- return column metadata
- return a preview of any sheet

Please keep the code modular.

I'd like separate services responsible for:

- dataset processing
- datatype detection
- metadata extraction
- preview generation

Please avoid putting business logic inside route files.

For the UI, continue using Bootstrap 5 and vanilla JavaScript.

Please add loading indicators while switching datasets or sheets.

If anything goes wrong, show friendly error messages instead of stack traces.

At the end, I'd also like a small statistics section showing things like:

- number of uploaded datasets
- total rows in the selected dataset
- total sheets
- total detected date columns
- total numeric columns

Please don't start implementing pivot tables yet.

This phase should only make the uploaded datasets reusable and prepare the application for the pivot engine in the next phase.

Once everything is finished, please provide:

- updated folder structure
- database schema
- API list
- any migrations required
- startup instructions if anything changed

